nodes.title: Invitation from the Emperor
nodes.description: Cayde's worried about a mysterious message drawing the Red Legion to a remote corner of Nessus.
"I wonder if the Vex even realize I hide stuff between the gaps in their block networks. Hmmm. Maybe that's how they know so much about me." —Cayde-6
"I guess I was afraid that Mind juice would somehow seize control of my weapons or something. That stuff isn't some kind of luxurious milk bath, trust me." —Cayde-6
"Of course, I didn't go charging into Nessus without a plan. I made sure I had caches everywhere. Started with the first dead Vex construct I found." —Cayde-6
"It was like I was being called closer, like something wanted my help. Then I get to this tower with a triangular doorway and go through. That's when it got really weird." —Cayde-6

nodes.description: "So after a full day of pulling loot out of the Fallen's hands, I thought I would just cool my engines down by that old river, but as soon as I cached it all up down there, a Servitor shows up." —Cayde-6

nodes.title: WANTED: Disgraced Bracus
nodes.description:

nodes.title: Anti-Anti-Air
nodes.description: Infiltrate the Red Legion base and disable their network of flak turrets.

"I used to have this old lookout. Scoped out my first FWC bunker there. Just like the Cabal to plop that eyesore of a base right on top of a piece of dark age nostalgia. Do me a favor, if you make it up there: snipe a few rhinos for me." —Cayde-6

nodes.description: Shut down the operations of an ironmonger providing weapons to the Red Legion.

nodes.description: Destroy the dark liquid that the Cabal use to power their technology or contaminate it, for a subtler approach.

nodes.title: Reversing the Polarity
nodes.description: The Cabal tend to use a single technology to power everything in their arsenal. Take advantage of that design flaw to send them a message.

nodes.title: Stop and Go
nodes.description: Power generators in the Red Legion base are open to attack—but only for a short time. Speed into the subterranean complex and shut them down.
"Stashed plenty of loot up at the old mill in the EDZ. To scare the Dregs off, I'd throw on some old Festival of the Lost masks and make 'em think the place was haunted." —Cayde-6

"They thought they had me dead-to-sights… backing me down this cliff. But I could see some fellow Hunters sparrowing in from the highway. Classic. So I sparked up a little Golden Gun and bought my guys some time.  I know I dropped something good in that one." —Cayde-6

nodes.description:

nodes.title: Payback
nodes.description:

Complete mission "Payback."

nodes.title: Dark Alliance
nodes.description: Red Legion Psions are meddling with forces best left alone. Investigate their connection to dark forces in the region.

nodes.title: Getting Your Hands Dirty
nodes.description: Seize upon the Taken invasion of the EDZ, direct their assault against the Red Legion, and end it before it gets out of control.

nodes.title: This Is For Your Own Goods
WANTED: Saturn Survivor
nodes.description:
Begin your hunt in the Sludge in the EDZ.
Hunt the surface of the EDZ for wanted escapees from the Prison of Elders.
"This place is full of old containers. Don't bother raiding them all—I already did. They're all filled with shoes. Mountains of Golden Age footwear, and not a thing in my size." —Cayde-6
"So once you get up there, don't be afraid to strut it on the catwalk. We both know the importance of looking good." —Cayde-6

"I've been all around this system, seen all sorts of transports, but nothing with the resiliency of this old Golden Age rustbucket I found in the EDZ. Used it as a grab-and-go spot for years." —Cayde-6
"OK, all I can give you to go on in this one is… it's high up. So… look up, I guess? Don't look at me like that, I'm doing my best.” —Cayde-6

"You do much driving? Me neither. But I used to spend nights hiding out near this truck just teetering on a ledge, just waiting for the day some dumb Dreg would send it over the ledge. That day never came." —Cayde-6
"So I took off edging the cliff, Golden Gun down to one shot. Left a lot behind cliffside. Bad day." —Cayde-6

"Listen, I feel bad making you go after my stuff, so last night I snuck down to the EDZ. Sh-sh-sh, don't tell Zavala! Anyway, I got the cache, then got a tiny bit turned around and ended up in a Cabal base. You know how that is. The dogs and all. Had to stash the goods quickly and get out. So… can you go get it?” —Cayde-6

nodes.title: The Arms Dealer
nodes.description:
Shut down the operations of an ironmonger providing weapons to the Red Legion.
Complete strike "The Arms Dealer."
"New lead from Hawthorne. Not really much to go on, something about a fan. I know I must have a lot of them, so if you see one down in the EDZ, maybe ask them?" —Cayde-6
“Good news: I remember exactly where one of my old EDZ caches is. Bad news: those parts are Taken territory now. So I guess the question is: how bad d'you want it?”

nodes.title: Brother Vance
nodes.description: A scholar and devout acolyte of the mysterious Osiris.
nodes.subtitle: Follower of Osiris

nodes.description: "Got it in my head to scale that canyon on Mercury, the one so deep you can't see the bottom. Left a stash on a ledge near the top. Shouldn't have to go too far to find it." —Cayde-6

nodes.title: The Up and Up
nodes.description: Prevent the Vex from completing a simulation of Fallen combat tactics.
"I have this feeling the Followers don't go outside much. Shame, too. If it was me, I'd be sunning myself on that patio thing they got going out there. Top-notch real estate." —Cayde-6

"Was actually trying to bring the Lighthouse some supplies. You know, since Almighty ate half the planet. But Vance wouldn't let me in! Couldn't find another way in, so I just left the stash near the door… near-ish." —Cayde-6
"They just kept warping in out of nowhere. I was handling it, you know, until—you get it. Anyway, I wasn't hiding behind the waterfall. Just regrouping." —Cayde-6
"Is it just me, or does the Lighthouse have a lot of broken doors? Well, if no one's using them as doors, I might as well use them as stash markers." —Cayde-6
"Good news: I left myself a note for this one. Bad news: the note just says 'live on the edge.' So… there you go." —Cayde-6
"I was trying to find a back door to the Infinite Forest. First place I looked? The actual back of the Forest door. No Vex doomsday machine, but I found a good spot for a stash." —Cayde-6
"So it's like a big stone ball, but it's got a fountain of radio-whatever on it. Don't look at me like that. I'm literally describing the topography." —Cayde-6

nodes.title: Bug in the System
nodes.description: Corrupt a Vex data-harvesting operation by withstanding an onslaught of Hive.

nodes.title: The Runner
nodes.description: Stop a Cabal simulation carrying heavily encrypted data.

nodes.title: Tree of Probabilities
nodes.description:
Now you know where to find the map of the Infinite Forest. Go and get it.
Complete mission "Tree of Probabilities."

nodes.title: Omega
nodes.description:
It's now or never. Enter the Infinite Forest and defeat Panoptes now, before the Vex future victory becomes inevitable.
Complete mission "Omega."

nodes.title: Signal Light
nodes.description: Locate the source of the familiar signal inside the Infinite Forest.

nodes.title: Beyond Infinity
nodes.description:
It's time to enter the Infinite Forest and find Osiris. Be prepared for anything.
Complete mission "Beyond Infinity."

nodes.title: Not Even the Darkness
nodes.description: Find Saint-14.

nodes.title: The Gateway
nodes.description:
Osiris's damaged Ghost appeared on Mercury—along with a Vex army. That can't be a coincidence.
Complete mission "The Gateway."

nodes.title: Tree of Probabilities
nodes.description:
Contain a rampant army of Red Legion within the Infinite Forest.
Complete strike "Tree of Probabilities."

nodes.title: A Garden World
nodes.description:
Help Osiris cut back an out-of-control Vex Mind.
Complete strike "A Garden World."

nodes.description:

Purchase bounties from the Spider to search Mercury for powerful wanted escapees from the Prison of Elders.

nodes.title: A Garden World
nodes.description:
Enter the Infinite Forest and steal the algorithm that will let you track Panoptes in the present.
Complete mission "A Garden World."
"Vance still won't let me in the Lighthouse! Can you believe it? Tried to hack that stupid door of his. Almost got it, too. Left some supplies behind for the next try." —Cayde-6

nodes.title: WANTED: Subterranean Mind
nodes.description:
Begin your hunt in Pariah's Refuge on Mercury.
Hunt the Lost Sector on Mercury for wanted escapees from the Prison of Elders.

nodes.description: Left scarred by his encounter with the Vex, the irascible Asher Mir holds Io for the Vanguard... and science.
nodes.subtitle: Fragmented Researcher

nodes.description: Investigate a mysterious broadcast that only you and your Ghost can hear.

nodes.title: Aphix Conduit

Loot the cache in the Aphix Conduit, a Lost Sector in the Rupture on Io.
Discover all Lost Sectors on Io.

nodes.title: Sanctum of Bones
nodes.description: Discover all Lost Sectors on Io.

"When I was caught in that Vex Teleporter, I would end up in weird places. Once or twice, I swear it was Io and saw one of my own caches on top one of those tall, pointy Vex things. That's all I got for you. That ‘porter was not a fun time!” —Cayde-6
"Do me a favor and just look into that Pyramidion thing, would you?  If the Vex are studying the best of humanity, you know they've got stuff on me in there.” —Cayde-6

"You know Eris Morn, right? Creepy three-eyed old Hunter, too much foundation? Doesn't matter. She comes in and asks me how Io was and I say, wrong Vanguard, ask Ikora; and she's like, I was hoping that cache by the bones marked your grave; and I'm like, I'm an Exo, I left my bones behind a long time ago; and she goes, exactly. You get anything from that?" —Cayde-6

"Funny thing, I know I've been to Io, but all the details are pretty hazy. Guess I'm getting old.  I have this memory of a battle on a bridge. Vex everywhere. After crossing a bridge, we took cover to the right, and then, well, it gets fuzzy from there. Maybe worth checking out?" —Cayde-6

nodes.title: The Pyramidion
nodes.description:
Seek vengeance against the Vex Mind that corrupted Asher's arm.
Complete strike "The Pyramidion."

nodes.title: Fury
nodes.description:
Help Ikora use the Warmind on Io to learn more about the Almighty—and turn the tide of the war.
Complete mission "Fury."

nodes.title: Deep Storage
nodes.description:
Search the Pyramidion on Io for a map of the Infinite Forest to guide you to Panoptes.
Complete mission "Deep Storage."

nodes.title: WANTED: Blood Cleaver
nodes.description:
Hunt down the wanted Blood Cleaver that escaped from the Prison of Elders.

nodes.title: Festival of the Lost… Sector
nodes.description: Amanda asked you to put on your mask and "show the bad guys they can't keep us down." What better place during this holiday season than the Sanctum of Bones?

nodes.title: Cliffhanger
nodes.description: Asher has information about the Vex's next conversion site, and he wants it stopped.

nodes.title: Postmodern Prometheus
nodes.description: Ikora is reluctantly allowing Asher to explore a plan where he'd convert the Traveler's energy into a form of synthetic Light.

nodes.title: WANTED: Blood Cleaver
nodes.description:
Hunt down the wanted Blood Cleaver that escaped from the Prison of Elders.
Purchase bounties from the Spider to search Io for powerful wanted escapees from the Prison of Elders.

nodes.title: Unexpected Guests
nodes.description: Ikora's worried about some Taken emanations from beneath the moon's surface.

nodes.title: Grove of Ulan-Tan
nodes.description:
Loot the cache in the Grove of Ulan-Tan, a Lost Sector in the Lost Oasis on Io.
Discover all Lost Sectors on Io.

"Asher called me to rant about a Taken Blight destroying a research wing of the Cabal base, and I'm like, why are you telling me? We're not friends; and then he mentions seeing one of my caches in the debris. Survived a Taken Blight. Not a bad design, if I do say so myself." —Cayde-6

"Damn Rhinos. Made off with everything from my lockers when they ransacked the Tower. This one here, they dragged to Io and apparently left it behind. Last ping I got came from their abandoned base on the Echo Mesa." —Cayde-6

"Gotta love the views on Io. I remember watching Jupiter float over the horizon, all big and stormy. I left a cache up there, and… fell asleep. Next thing I know, my Ghost's reviving me at the base of the cliff. Guess I roll around in my sleep.” —Cayde-6

nodes.title: WANTED: Ghaul Devotee
nodes.description:
Begin your hunt in the Lost Oasis on Io.
Hunt the surface of Io for wanted escapees from the Prison of Elders.

nodes.title: Sacrilege
nodes.description: Since the loss of her Light, Ikora has many questions—and she's not leaving Io without answers.

nodes.title: Road Rage
nodes.description: Asher's worked up about Vex interest in the Io Vault. He's got an unusual suggestion for how to deal with the problem.

"The lead I got from Asher was some Psion was seen making off with this one somewhere in the Echo Mesa. He mumbled something about it being on top of some Cabal checkpoint, before it—well—fell into a pit of Taken. And we all know how that turns out." —Cayde-6

"I got word on another cache in the Echo Mesa. Some of Asher's 'assistants' chased a Legionary out of the Cabal Base but lost him in a little cave nearby. Must've left it there, since the rhino came out empty handed. That's when the assistants got him. Good thing, 'cause I'd rather it go to you." —Cayde-6

nodes.title: Xûr
nodes.description: A peddler of strange curios, Xûr's motives are not his own. He bows to his distant masters, the Nine.
nodes.subtitle: Agent of the Nine

nodes.description: "You ever talk to Banshee much? He's got this saying: Sometime the deeper you go, the less you'll ever understand. The Cabal are kind of like that. Why they feel the need to drag my stuff into their damn Io base… beyond me." —Cayde-6

"OK, another live cache report here… Gotta give the Cabal credit. They're great at digging tunnels. Then again, so are worms… and snakes… and woodchucks… and crabs... and ants… ugh, I hate ants." —Cayde-6

"OK, so, Albios's memorial service was on Io. Sacred to Warlocks, blah blah blah. Don't get me wrong, I liked Al—but the service ran a bit long. Ended up betting Banshee I could make a few hairy jumps high up on the Mesa. Broke both my legs, but I did it. I forget what Banshee gave me, but I know I left it in a cache up there somewhere.” —Cayde-6

"Have you ever had a dream you're in this cave full of mist and you see this amazing cache, but every time you reach to open it, a new layer of mists blocks your path? No? Am I the only one who has this dream?" —Cayde-6

"So word is one of the Cabal's drill engineers found another one of my caches. I don't know if I did such a good job sealing it or if those dumb rhino fingers are too fat to pry it open. Anyway, it's been spotted in some hole near that drill site. I guess Ghaul called them back before they could get into it." —Cayde-6

nodes.description: A veteran of many battlefields, Sloane oversees operations on Titan.
nodes.subtitle: Field Commander

nodes.title: Thief of Thieves
nodes.description: Recover the supplies that the Fallen have taken.

nodes.title: Methane Flush
nodes.description: Loot the cache in the Methane Flush, a Lost Sector in Siren's Watch on Titan.
"I always used Titan as a rest stop before hitting the Reef. Something about those waves. This one's right under your nose. And your feet." —Cayde-6

"Getting pings on another one somewhere high up in one of those towers. From what I hear, the Fallen are using those towers as some kind of junkyard. Could be like a needle in a haystack. Good luck.” —Cayde-6

nodes.title: WANTED: Hiraks's Familiar
nodes.description:

"So I chased the gang of Awoken thieves up to the Arcology. That bridge didn't look too stable, and I'm not into methane baths, so I stashed what I had and picked up their trail inside." —Cayde-6

nodes.title: Would You Like to Know More

nodes.description: "Reef Awoken are weird like that. She assured me it was a gold mine, so I went exploring. Check near some kind of generator machine thing, there should be one I haven't hit in years." —Cayde-6

nodes.title: Deathless
nodes.description: Clear out the Knight that's keeping Sloane's crews from their work.

nodes.title: Savathûn's Song
nodes.description:
Delve deep into the Hive-infested Arcology in search of missing fireteams.
Complete strike "Savathûn's Song."

nodes.title: Utopia
nodes.description:
Venture deep into the heart of the Hive to retrieve a powerful Golden Age CPU—and make it out alive.
Complete mission "Utopia."

nodes.title: WANTED: Gravetide Summoner
nodes.description:
Hunt down the wanted Gravetide Summoner who escaped from the Prison of Elders.
Purchase bounties from the Spider to search Titan for powerful wanted escapees from the Prison of Elders.

nodes.title: WANTED: Gravetide Summoner
nodes.description:
Hunt down the wanted Gravetide Summoner who escaped from the Prison of Elders.
Purchase bounties from the Spider to search Titan for powerful wanted escapees from the Prison of Elders.
"This one is in some kind of wall. What was it with the Golden Age that they built walls around everything?" —Cayde-6
"What idiot crashed the tank into the wall? It definitely, one hundred percent, absolutely wasn't me. You believe me, right?" —Cayde-6
"Mapping these pings to the latest from Sloane, looks like you'll be tearing through some kind of ceiling garden. Good luck with that.” —Cayde-6

"You know what I used to love about my rest stops on Titan? Walking into the Arcology and thinking about it in its heyday. But then you get to thinking of how much we actually lost, and now the Hive just spawning everywhere… and the will to fight boils right back up." —Cayde-6
"So this cache… all I remember is it's in a very… blue room. You'll know it when you see it." —Cayde-6

"Those Fallen on Titan. I've been after them for years. They ransacked an old trove I kept in the Sink on Venus, then went completely dark. Getting pings on one, but everyone who's been after it gets lost in the dark way down below." —Cayde-6
"And just to amuse myself I would find natural x's in any environment and stash something somewhere beneath them, just to be able to say those words to myself… 'X marks the spot.'”
"I take it you like to jump, right? I see the way you jump all around the Tower. Guardians these days—no respect for gravity." —Cayde-6
"OK, I actually made a sketch to remind me of this one. And it looks like I put it… near some kind of windmill. Or fan. Or something." —Cayde-6

Complete mission "Hope."
